# Documentation Rules

## OpenAPI Documentation
Update [src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml](mdc:src/main/resources/openapi/documentation.yaml) for new endpoints:

```yaml
/api/endpoint:
  get:
    operationId: getEndpoint
    tags: [ TagName ]
    summary: Brief description
    description: Detailed description
    security:
      - BearerAuth: []
    responses:
      "200":
        description: Success description
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              allOf:
                - $ref: "#/components/schemas/BasicApiResponse"
                - type: object
                  properties:
                    data:
                      $ref: "#/components/schemas/ResponseModel"
      "400":
        description: Bad request
      "401":
        description: Unauthorized
```

## Postman Collection
Update [postman_collection.json](mdc:postman_collection.json) for new endpoints:

```json
{
  "name": "Endpoint Name",
  "request": {
    "method": "GET",
    "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}"}],
    "url": {
      "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/endpoint",
      "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
      "path": ["api", "endpoint"]
    },
    "description": "Endpoint description"
  }
}
```

## Documentation Requirements
- Include examples for both success and error responses
- Document authorization requirements clearly
- Update both Swagger and Postman when adding endpoints
- Include request/response schemas
- Document validation rules and error codes